      "title": "[DC] reya.li@🔸lore-chat: i personally think that chapter 1 probably still has the best average quality of",
      "summary": "i personally think that chapter 1 probably still has the best average quality of dialogue and character expression mostly because it focused on a very small and confined story compared to the other chapters, doll is also a very engaging character in general and (at least within her chapter 1 appearances) is far better written than say clementine\n\nbut honestly chapter 5 is by far the most fun and zesty chapter so it's probably my favorite, even though it would be fair to critique that it's a little bloated, the philosophical discussion is a bit undercooked (for example: treating a theoretical utopia that would eventually be doomed as automatically worse than a maybe-not-doomed shitty reality without expanding on that point at all) as well as the final setpiece fight being kind of... narratively unnecessary? lesbian jazz bar hours and bosnian coffee make up for it",
